CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1959, pg. 1 reads: "Admits Guilt - Nineteen-year-old Walter Joseph Phillips of Sciota St., Bloomfield, leaves the courtroom in custody of two deputies, after he admitted to brutal robbery-murder of 80-year-old Green Evans of 434 Fisk St., last July 28. In an East Liberty alley off Shakespeare St. near the Cameraphone Theatre. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two police officers handcuffed to Walter Joseph Phillips, after admitting to robbery and murder, exiting door inscribed 323 in corridor of the Allegheny County Courthouse
